<HEAD>Barges Drift On River, One Hits Bridge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BURNSIDE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ninety-one barges broke loose from a
Mississippi River terminal and at least one hit the base of the
Sunshine Bridge, forcing its closure for more than two hours.
   No one was hurt and nothing leaked from the barges, officials
said.
   Dempsey Edmonston, dock supervisor for Burnside Terminal, said
the barges were moored two miles upriver from the bridge when they
got loose Sunday.
   All were rounded up and secured within a couple hours, the Coast
Guard said.
   There were unconfirmed reports that the wake from a passing ship
tore the barge loose.
