<SECOND>PM-Fatal Fire,0215</SECOND>
<HEAD>Five Die In Weekend Apartment Blaze</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELPRE, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who fled an apartment fire that
claimed five lives was arrested after screaming at firefighters to
save people trapped inside, police say.
   One woman, however, credited the man's yells early Saturday
morning with saving her and her family.
   Larry Bishop, 29, was charged with disorderly conduct, which
carries a $50 fine.
   ``He was carrying on, trying to give orders to everybody,'' said
police Capt. Ronald Burch. ``He's not a fireman, nor is he a
policeman.''
   Ruth Farr said Bishop's shouts awakened her and her husband in
time for them and their three children to get out.
   ``He was shouting, `Come on, don't die up there! Come out! Come
out!''' said Ms. Farr. ``He went crazy trying to get people out.
The cops kind of had to wrestle him to the ground, but if it wasn't
for him hollering, we wouldn't have woken up.''
   The three adults and two children killed in the blaze were found
on the second floor of the two-story apartment. Bishop said he had
been asleep on a first-floor couch after attending a party for one
of the women who later died.
   The cause of the fire was under investigation.
