<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--ElvisHome     04-24 0192</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Elvis Home,0197</SECOND>
<HEAD>Elvis House: Move With Care</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who owns a house in which Elvis
Presley and his parents once lived wants someone to buy it and move
it off its lot by May 1, but he wants the work done ``with love and
care.''
   Presley and his parents lived in the small brick house from
mid-1955 until May 1956, said David Isom.
   Isom said Sunday he wants to sell the home for $45,000 or more
and remove it from the property. An auto parts store is to be built
on the property.
   ``If this was Elvis week, somebody would show up and buy it
piece by piece and reassemble it at home,'' Isom said.
   Isom installed a sign in the front yard proclaiming: ``Elvis
Presley Lived Here _ 1955-56 _ House For Sale _ Move With Love &amp;
Care.''
   The Presley estate contacted Isom about possibly acquiring the
house and moving it to the grounds of Presley's Graceland estate in
Memphis, he said.
   ``The estate called and they were looking for a gift,'' Isom
said. ``This is not a charity; this is a business.''
