<HEAD>Steven Spielberg-Amy Irving Divorce Disclosed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Director Steven Spielberg and actress Amy
Irving have decided to divorce, ending months of speculation that
their 3{-year marriage was on the rocks.
   ``The settlement agreements have already been amicably reached
by both Ms. Irving and Mr. Spielberg,'' publicist Robert G.
Friedman said Monday while issuing a statement from the couple.
   ``We have decided to make this statement public in order to
protect the privacy of our family, which is of great importance to
us,'' the statement said. Supermarket tabloids have speculated on a
split for months.
   ``Our mutual decision, however difficult, has been made in the
spirit of caring. And our friendship remains both personal and
professional,'' the statement concluded.
   Spielberg, 40, and Miss Irving, 35, were married in November
1985 in a private civil ceremony in Santa Fe, N.M. They have a
3-year-old son, Max.
   Details on child custody arrangements and division of property
weren't disclosed, said Friedman.
   Among Spielberg's hit films as a director or producer are
``Jaws,'' ``Close Encounters of the Third Kind,'' ``Raiders of the
Lost Ark,'' ``E.T. _ The Extra-Terrestrial,'' ``Empire of the
Sun,'' ``The Color Purple'' and ``Who Framed Roger Rabbit.''
   Ms. Irving's movie credits included ``Honeysuckle Rose,''
``Crossing Delancey'' and she was nominated for a supporting
actress Oscar in ``Yentl.''
