<HEAD>Premature Quintuplets Cling To Life</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROYAL OAK, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Premature quintuplets, all girls,
remained in critical condition Monday at William Beaumont Hospital,
officials said.
   The girls, ranging in weight from 14{ to 16{ ounces, were born
between 7:38 and 7:40 p.m. Saturday to Nina Gambino, 26, of Utica,
hospital spokeswoman Valerie Mahaczek said.
   Marie, Michelle, Alyssa, Dana and Natalie Gambino were delivered
15 weeks early by Lenny Hutton, who said the infants were conceived
naturally while Mrs. Gambino was taking the fertility drug Pergonal.
   Nina and Frank Gambino, 27, have no other children, hospital
officials said.
   Two other sets of quintuplets have been born in the past 16
months in metropolitan Detroit. Michelle L'Esperance of Clarkston
gave birth to four girls and a boy conceived through in vitro
fertilization on Jan. 12, 1988, at Beaumont Hospital. Mary Jo
Wilson of Auburn Hills gave birth to three girls and two boys on
Jan. 5 at Sinai Hospital in Detroit. All survived.
