<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-ITT     04-24 0192</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-ITT,0200</SECOND>
<HEAD>ITT Earnings Rise 12 Percent In Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ITT Corp.'s profit rose 12 percent in the first
quarter on a 6 percent increase in revenue, the conglomerate said
Monday.
   ITT said it earned $200 million, or $1.40 a share, up from $180
million, or $1.25 a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose to $4.8
billion from $4.5 billion.
   Tax benefits at The Hartford insurance unit added $8 million to
the 1989 quarter's net income and $12 million to that of the 1988
quarter, ITT said.
   Revenue in the 1988 quarter was restated to reflect an insurance
accounting standard adopted at the end of 1988. The change did not
affect net income figures.
   ITT said all its service businesses registered gains except for
the Hartford, whose results reflected a general downturn in
domestic property and casualty underwriting. Sheraton Corp., ITT's
hotel segment, registered strong gains, mainly in Europe and Asia,
it said.
   On the product side, operating results improved in the
automotive, defense and fluid technology businesses, while
electronics' components results remained basically the same.
Alcatel NV, 37 percent owned by ITT, contributed higher earnings,
ITT said.
</TEXT>
