<SECOND>BC-Earns-Retail,0201</SECOND>
<HEAD>Melville Posts 8 Percent First-Quarter Profit Growth</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Melville Corp., owner of specialty retail stores across the
country, Monday reported a 7.9 percent increase in its
first-quarter income.
   The Harrison, N.Y.-based retailer said its after-tax earnings
totaled $24.2 million in the three months ended April 1, up from
$22.5 million in the corresponding period a year earlier.
   On a per-share basis, earnings came to 22 cents in this year's
first quarter compared with a restated 21 cents in 1988. Melville
stock was split Feb. 23.
   Sales amounted to $1.53 billion in the first quarter, an
increase of 9.7 percent from $1.39 billion in the first quarter of
1988, which had two more selling days than this year's first
quarter.
   Melville said the acquisition of Bermans Specialty Stores Inc.
in the fourth quarter of 1988 adversely impacted the first
quarter's operating results.
   Among the stores owned by Melville are Thom McAn shoe shops, the
off-price brand name apparel chain Marshalls, CVS drug stores,
Linens 'N Things and This End Up furniture stores. These and other
Melville-owned stores totaled 6,744 as of April 1, up from 6,117 a
year earlier.
