<HEAD>Martin Marietta Earnings up 12.6 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BETHESDA, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Martin Marietta Corp. reported Monday its
first-quarter earnings rose 16.2 percent as its sales edged up 1.6
percent.
   Martin Marietta said its earnings for the first three months
totaled $59.2 million, or $1.12 per share, up from $50.9 million,
or 96 cents per share, in the same period of last year.
   Sales for the quarter increased to $1.32 billion from nearly
$1.3 billion in the first quarter of 1988.
   The gains reflect strong performances by the two largest groups
within Martin Marietta, the astronautics and electronics and
missiles divisions, said Norman R. Augustine, chairman and chief
executive.
   ``Overall results are in line with expectations and support our
belief that full 1989 earnings will show further growth over
normalized 1988 earnings,'' Augustine said.
   Martin Marietta is an aerospace and information technology
company with more than 70,000 employees.
