<SECOND>BC-Earns-Tire,0220</SECOND>
<HEAD>Goodyear, Uniroyal Goodrich Sales Up In First Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   First-quarter sales increased at both
Goodyear Tire &amp; Rubber Co. and Uniroyal Goodrich Tire Co., but
profits were down slightly at Goodyear, while Uniroyal Goodrich
trimmed its net loss compared with the first quarter of last year.
   In the three months ending March 31, Goodyear earned $94.5
million, or $1.64 a share, on sales of $2.6 billion, the company
said Monday.
   In the same period of 1988, Goodyear earned $95.3 million, or
$1.67 a share, on sales of $2.5 billion.
   Chairman Tom H. Barrett said results from the company's U.S.
tire operations improved and sales of industrial and chemical
products were strong.
   Uniroyal Goodrich had a net loss of $7 million in the 1989
quarter, compared with a loss of $7.6 million in the first quarter
of 1988. Sales for the quarter were $537.6 million, up from $482.8
million during the comparable period last year.
   The loss was produced by additional interest expense from last
year's restructuring, which wiped out operating profits, the
company said.
   ``This net loss reflects the expected seasonality of our tire
business and is not indicative of our anticipated full year
results,'' said Sheldon R. Salzman, company president and chief
operating officer.
